  "datePublished": "2026-03-06",
  "description": "An ***unreliable narrator*** is a [narrator](./narrator.md) whose account of events the reader has reason to doubt. [Wayne Booth](../../../../general/domains/people/wayne-booth.md) introduced the concept in *The Rhetoric of Fiction* (1961): a narrator is unreliable when their norms — their values, perceptions, or knowledge — diverge from the norms the text as a whole implies [@booth1961].",
